                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 840.48/9: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-07T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 7, 1919—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 8—5 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>131. For President from Glass. Transmitted to Congress your request for one
                    hundred million dollar appropriation to relieve starvation in Europe. I took up
                    matter in advance with Democratic leaders of Senate and House and am hopeful
                    authority will be granted.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
